column5: I'll be leaving Friday night or early Saturday morning from Mississauga, making a stop in west end Toronto to pick up the boat. Driving down solo.  Ya, I know.    Waited too long, last minute, no space, all booked, ..... Guess I may have to sacrifice my body in the name of fishing and shack up with the local cougars if I can't get a floor spot. Ahhh, life is good in Canada....no ???  I'm waiting to hear back from blackfish88, so I'll have room for 1 or possibly 2 in the boat. Let me know if anyone needs a boat to fish in. Anyone want to fish with the best walleye guide in the world ? Well, he's probably busy, so you can fish with me instead.   By the way, I like the look of the new site. Nice job guys.
Ladywalley needs a spot on a boat.  I'll see if I can get ahold of her.  Joey
The local cougars hang out at JJ's Bar and Grill in Bloomfiled.  Saw a nasty mess of them a couple weeks ago.
No problem Joey.  It would be a pleasure to have her aboard.   @ Fang.
Heading down to Quinte in the wee hours - any word today from the guys already down there?    Don

Headin to BOQ real early Buddy of mine gets off his night shift at 1:30 getting in his car and driving from Cambridge meeting me at the house and were takin off to hook up with Lloyd for some MONSTER EYES. Cheers boys & girls suppose to be nice no Rain no Wind WOO HO

Real sad you got stood up like the ugly girl on prom night Remo! Just don't understand people sometimes. Lots of screw ups at Quinte this year in my honest opinion...I really don't get how some people think.
